Eating children suffering from obesity: No breakfast and sausage for dinner.
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 weigh more than normal; while 9% of schoolchildren are overweight, 5% suffer from obesity.
According to the latest study, children who suffer from obesity usually come from families who lead an unhealthy lifestyle.
We again see the importance of the environment and the patterns of behavior associated with a person for his or her healthy development.
For example, sausages appear on the tables of children suffering from obesity, almost twice as often as in families with children with normal weight.
More than 19% of children suffering from obesity ate frozen potatoes for dinner on the eve of a survey related to an educational event called Obesity is not a coincidence.
Moreover, families of children suffering from obesity do not engage in sports. This, however, concerns the majority of families of modern schoolchildren - only 15% of children said that their parents find time for sports at least once a week.
The study was conducted among 900 children.
The study was conducted at the end of last academic year; it was attended by almost 900 elementary school students throughout Bohemia.
The Obesity event is not a coincidence held for the second year in a row, with the support of the insurance company V<0xC5><0xA1>eobecn<0xC3><0xA1> <0xC5><0xBD>edotn<0xC3><0xAD> poji<0xC5><0xA1>tovna and the company Unilever.
To date, more than 12,000 students in grades 4 to 8 have joined the project.
Proper nutrition and adequate sports load are the main determining factors that cause a rapidly growing number of children who suffer from either excess weight or from obesity.
“For example, only half of the respondents said they ate five times a day on the breakfast-percussion-lunch-percussion-dinner scheme, which is one of the inevitable conditions of proper nutrition,” the study said.
No lunch and sausage at night.
Experts warn that even relative details such as the constant time of a family breakfast are important for healthy development.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of schoolchildren’s families have breakfast together.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast separately.
The worst finding is that in one in ten families, people don’t eat breakfast at all.
And yet breakfast is the basis of the correct daily diet.
The study showed that fried food is more commonly consumed in families with children suffering from obesity.
Almost everyone – regardless of weight – drinks sweet chilled drinks every day (70%).
Although more than 40% of children regularly engage in sports, this figure is more than double — up to 15% — when it comes to their parents.
Create your own menu.
In the second part of the study, selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) were asked to make their own menu based on the products offered and based on their tastes and preferences.
"Preferences in food in Czech children aged 12-15 years are far from ideal in terms of healthy eating."
Their favorite food includes a large number of spicy, meaty and sweet foods.
“A particular concern is the high popularity of sweet chilled drinks,” says the final part of the study.
As the main meal of the meal, the paste defeated the bird with a small excess weight.
However, the children showed almost no interest in bean, fish and vegetable dishes.
Aspiration to a healthy lifestyle
The study also showed that children are willing to change their eating habits provided they are provided with relevant information.
“Many participants in the control group of the study showed a significant shift in preferences towards healthy food when they filled out a questionnaire after the conclusion of the Obesity lecture – it’s no coincidence,” says the results of the project.
This was especially noticeable, for example, in the case of sweet chilled drinks - more children began to prefer them just water.
In addition, as the main dish, children were more likely to notice birds and fish, limiting the number of sweet dishes and baked goods.
A stylist should also be a good psychologist, say professionals
In the first article about trainings for stylists, I sat on the volume of information at introductory classes.
I had no idea what would happen next.
Lectures by three experts in this field; advice on choosing clothes for non-standard figures; and a seminar on how all this works in real life.
Next is more.
The closer we get to the final exam, the more information and practical tasks await us.
The training is held every Saturday and Sunday, but it is really full of information.
This time with Alenka, the director, (there is not a single man on the course) we discussed how to dress a woman whose body is not perfectly symmetrical.
Most women are not completely symmetrical.
With one short neck, with another boy figure with no proper shapes, another weighs more than the norm.
The stylist should know how to visually reduce the wide shoulders, lengthen the neck, or add missing volumes.
We were given advice on how to emphasize the figure of women like Jennifer Lopez, i.e. the owners of a more lush chest and thigh and narrow waist, and at the same time not to dress them too provocatively.
For example, if the difference in the size of the waist and waistband is so large that you can not pick up a skirt or pants, it is worth having at least one thing sewn to order.
You will obviously not regret the invested funds, as the perfectly sitting clothes are priceless.
In a skirt, sewn to order, you will feel much better than in the one that constantly moves, curls, exposes the waist, etc.
The owners of boys' figures, on the other hand, can wear clothes with ruffles, appliques, embroidery or folds.
Given the abundance of such information and types of figures, I am glad that I have a whole week to realize it all.
And yet, I'm afraid, it's too much, given the homework we've got.
Each participant of the courses had to come up with two outfits for any celebrity: for the day and for the evening.
We must take into account their modern appearance, their style in clothes and the type of figure.
I'm going to wear Miranda Kerr, which you may know about the Victoria's Secret advertising campaign.
I’m happy about myself because it’s a lot easier to wear than, say, Britney Spears, Kristina Aguilera, who has recently corrected herself to a ton (please keep in mind that I’m exaggerating), or quite young Selena Gomez.
We have to cut clothes out of magazines or find them on the Internet, print and process them using graphic programs.
The mudboard - so called the result of the work - then reflects our own style and attitude to the graphic image.
It is important to keep in mind the graphic composition style.
The stylist not only dresses real people, but creates product pages in magazines (based on special instructions, for example, fashion bags, coats, etc.).
This is what stylist and designer Mario Camenik told us.
But it was only on Sunday.
Stylists need common knowledge.
The Saturday lecture, filled with information about the types of figures, was revived by three guests - specialists in this field.
A stylist, Honza Suborna; a fashion designer, Jacob Polanka; and a fashion photographer Ben Ranch.
Jacob reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist must use this fact.
A good stylist can use one item of clothing in different ways.
In this case, diversity is the key to success.
For example, a t-shirt can be worn in the usual way, on top of jeans and t-shirts, like a coat; but it can also be worn on a naked body, without laces, like a dress.
Another option is to fold the sleeve or raise the collar, and the whole image changes completely.
"Play with him," he said.
Anyway, I most appreciated the following advice: “For your work, you should know the rules perfectly.”
Then you can start to break them,” Jacob told us.
Here I finally understood why we are going to brush up on all the definitions and rules, what to combine with what and why, while in fashion magazines we often see quite different.
Not to mention fashion shows.
From Ben, the photographer, I learned that the stylist must have more options for outfits than the number of photos he needs to take.
So, for a fashion review on ten pages (equivalent to ten outfits) I have to be ready to create at least fifteen images.
Now I also know that in the picture the subject of clothing often looks and works in combination with others quite differently than in reality.
We have to keep that in mind when we create an image.
Honza Suborna confirmed that often the image and style are half the success.
Just look at Madonna, who doesn’t have an amazing vocal, but her image and marketing have turned her into a world star.
The attitude to the services of stylists in the Czech Republic is still quite cool.
Even famous people often consider it unnecessary (and believe that it is enough to be a specialist in something, and what they look like - secondary).
And if someone finally allows us to create their style, we should expect them to call us a different (less) size than the one they really wear.
Then we turn to Google and find out if the tabloids have written anything about the fact that some celebrity ceiling/weight, etc.
On Sunday, Honza and Mario emphasized that it is not enough for the stylist to understand fashion and be able to choose clothes.
Our job consists mainly of communicating with the people we dress; therefore, it is important to be a good psychologist.
To be able to evaluate people, not to bully them and stick to their opinions.
“If the manager asks you to look at her clothes and add some beautiful things, you can’t throw away her entire wardrobe by telling her that her clothes are terrible.”
“Find at least a few things you can praise, and advise what you can wear with them,” says Mario.
He also showed us that a work bag should be placed specifically.
This is the bag that you tie around the waist to wear everything you need.
In addition to obvious things, such as scissors, sticky roller or English pins, it should have a nylon thread (stylers use it when shooting some items, for example, a bag or hat), special clips for fastening the fabric to the back of the shoe, if the buckle is worn
In order to get away from the lectures and get some practical experience, we learned how to properly make linings on the soles of the shoes.
Even during filming in a studio where the floor is smooth, the soles can get damaged - not to mention the shots on the street.
And here's what we did with the sticker.
You should not touch the shoes with scissors to avoid spoiling them.
This requires a real skill.
I was glad that Mario praised my work.
These skills did not come to my mind.
This is only part of what we heard during the second part of the weekend courses.
I’m beginning to understand that being a professional stylist isn’t as easy as they say.
V Need for Speed: Escape takes place in America.
Review
What was supposed to be a carefree walk turned into a routine morning trip to work due to a series of completely inappropriate and careless mistakes.
Ambitions to some extent were met, but that doesn’t matter, as no one clearly wanted to do extra work.
Before the release of the new version with the subtitle "Run" connected great hopes.
It was expected to move previous Need For Speed series in a new direction; demo versions have indicated that the game will take a decent place in the racing game genre.
We were curious to see parts of the game where the main character gets out of the car and runs away.
As is often the case with NFS, in the end, a lot is different from what we expected.
The game is a pretty good arcade race, but the overall impression is marred by several unnecessary mistakes that have been present in this series of games for several years.
So, in fact, this is not a mistake, but an inexplicable glitch of developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You become part of the story, whose main character, Jack, decides to solve some personal problems by participating in an illegal race through America.
You get in a car on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your task is to get to New York first.
This idea has several interesting features.
The route consists of ten stages, divided into more than fifty races.
This means that each race takes place on its own route, individual stages take place in a diverse and interesting environment.
There’s no sense in the game that the same thing happens all the time.
Despite the fact that the schedule is on the same level as in the previous parts of the series, on some routes it is nice to watch.
The game does not cause strong emotions.
Although driving a car through the desert, in the autumn suburbs or high in the snowy mountains is very pleasant.
In addition, racing from time to time revives an unusual detail.
For example, in the desert you get into a sandstorm, significantly reducing visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you need to be careful not to get under the avalanche.
The individual races are quite well-ordered.
There are only a few varieties, but that is enough.
For some time you are trying to overtake several opponents (essentially a regular race); then you are trying to improve the time (the standard race with a second timer); or you are competing with one opponent.
In addition, from time to time you come across a police force that complicates your task even more.
The exterior of the car is new.
It’s just an interactive animation where most of Jack’s time is running away from someone and you have to help him by pressing the right buttons at the right time.
It's not complicated.
Although it’s surprising that these fragments are much smaller than you might expect (just three to be exact).
In fact, it turns out that it’s good for the game because this property doesn’t add up; given all the above, it’s one of the things that makes the game more fun.
The racing model follows the tracks of previous models.
This means that it no longer represents something special, but it cannot be considered a disadvantage.
If you are looking for an imitation of real life, you will have to look elsewhere.
And yet this driving model is very suitable for dynamic races, although better options can be found on the market.
So far, it's all very good.
After a while, however, problems begin.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not so good.
From such a game you do not expect complex transformations and collisions, but if you do not have the concepts before the collision with the object, how will your machine behave, something is wrong.
Usually, driving or driving past machines in a tight flow, you sometimes slightly touch the other machine. And yet sometimes in a practically similar situation, your machine starts to spin furiously.
Or it broke into pieces.
This is not so important thanks to the reboot system, but it is enough to spoil the fun.
Restarts are arranged so that if you break down or leave the track far away, the game returns you to the point where it was interrupted.
However, only five restarts are available for each race.
If you use them all, you will have to start the race from the beginning.
This is useful if something doesn’t work out, but you can’t fully rely on it.
Sometimes restarts are not enough, and you have to learn a separate section of the race by accident.
An important disadvantage of the game is the fact that the same things often happen in the same places.
For example, some turns need to go through a certain way, otherwise you just won’t sign up.
In other cases, you encounter civilian cars in a specific location in the same configuration regardless of whether you arrive first, fifth, for five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is especially annoying in situations where you see your opponent easily travel between two machines moving in the opposite direction, while when you are there, the machines are already arranged so that you either need to wrap them around or drop the speed.
It doesn’t matter when you get close to them; everything is arranged so that the situation always happens just in front of your nose.
Competitors also have other advantages.
During the game you discover several places where, regardless of the time, the same opponent chases you in the same place.
This is especially evident at the end of the game, on the long bridge where you go in the opposite direction.
Obviously, your opponent has to stand before you no matter what.
The fact is that when it goes in front of you, it worsens your review, which leads to one or more accidents on this site.
You can understand the attempt to make the game more interesting and full of adrenaline, but it’s so obvious that it quickly starts to cause irritation.
Unfortunately, because despite the simple driving model, the game is fun and sometimes so packed with events that you don’t have time to pay attention to what’s going on around you.
It doesn’t matter what doesn’t let you miss – a concept with fifty unique tracks, a sequence of races or something else.
The idea of changing cars during races is unusual.
You need to track the ignitions along the way, because it is on them that your car can change, despite the fact that in most cases the one you already have is quite enough.
The machines are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for cities; powerful American cars are for straight sections of the highway; and exotic super-sporters for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain trails.
The main story mode is closely related to the challenge mode; these are individual sections races that you will learn during the course of the game.
Here you win for your personal business both medals and points, common to the modes of challenges and story.
Many options are available to get a higher level of driving: starting from the machines and ending with the profile data.
In addition, the profile is associated with the online Autolog function, which, among other things, compares the results you have achieved with the results of other players, and provides communication with the public.
Here is another drawback that is difficult to understand; this is an example of the last race in a sequence.
You and your car will get into the subway tunnel (we’ll think so), where you’ll race along the tracks in the dark (we’ll think so).
Your speedometer shows the figures from 150 to 200 km/h (we’ll assume that is so), when suddenly a subway train hits you from behind, turning your car into a bust of a metallolobra.
For a few days, our editorial team discussed whether no one really thought for a second while creating the game, or whether its creators really consider us such buffaloes.
The technical component of the game is nothing special; but the overall impression of the video series is mostly pleasant, sometimes even amazing.
Although, unfortunately, at some critical moments, the quality of the recording, sometimes quite strongly, decreases.
This is especially true of events with a large number of participants, where a good recording would not help you too.
The sound is fine; the soundtrack is for the lover.
In order to please as wide a youth as possible, the soundtrack has 'compositions of different styles'; but it is unlikely that many people will buy the game because of its music.
The general impression of Need for Speed: Escape is quite messy.
If the game avoided clearly unnecessary errors, we could honestly say that Escape is the best part of NFS in the last few years.
Either way, the game leaves the feeling of infinity.
Of course, it’s a good entertainment, but be prepared for the drawbacks that will blind you as an airport projector.
