He has a vision of what things could and should have been.
Soon after he said everything here, he went and did it.
A brief summary of the seven significant conclusions of the Lost Interview:
About how he learned to run a business:
“During all this time in business, I’ve been constantly asking, ‘Why are you doing this?’ and the answers you’re constantly getting are, ‘Oh, it’s just done that way.’
No one knows why they do what they do, no one thinks very deeply in business.
