Jobs continues to describe in detail his attempts to rationalize reporting at Apple.
Disturbed by the way of recording expenses, often starting with “standard expenses” that were taken from the ceiling and then adjusted by means of “accuracy”, he created an automated structure that ensured that they would be able to track business expenses up to the smallest.
A joke about the Pope:
Jobs tells in detail about the "blue box" he mastered with Steve Wozniak, a device that allowed people to effectively break into the phone company and call large distances for free.
