We both knew a little bit, but we could master a little thing that could control a big thing – it was an incredible lesson, and I don’t think that without it, Apple could ever have appeared.
Jobs goes on to describe in detail one of the famous getaways he and Wozniak have practically managed to cope with by calling the Vatican through a blue box at midnight and asking the Pope’s phone to try to copy Henry Kissinger.
When different members of the Catholic hierarchy were called in the middle of the night to talk to the American diplomat, the two were outraged by laughter just before the Pope himself was raised to answer the phone.
About the love of technology (and Bill Hullett's cold calling):
